\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
APRS Transmitter
\series default
 Leverages existing radio relays to keep payload in constant contact after
 takeoff; will send all data (except for photographs) to ground station
 in real-time; also equipped with GPS capable of high altitude positioning
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
MicroSD Card
\series default
 Storage capacity of 256GB (3 million photos or 33 hours of HD video) All
 sensor data will be saved to this, including live video and photographs
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
Internal Sensors 
\series default
Pressure, Temperature, and Humidity
\series bold
: 
\series default
Data collected from these sensors is written onto the Micro SD Card AND
 sent to the ground in real-time via the APRS transmitter
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
Accelerometer 
\series default
Data from the accelerometer is also written to the MicroSD card and sent
 to the ground via APRS
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
GPS 
\series default
Secondary GPS on separate power source, provides 100% location redundancy
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
Bluetooth Transmitter 
\series default
Power consumption by transmitter almost negligible; transmission does not
 interfere with APRS
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
External Camera 
\series default
13MP Live video and photographs written to MicroSD Card; possibility of
 transmitting photos in real-time via digital APRS band
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
External Sensors 
\series default
Pressure and temperature:
\series bold
 
\series default
These sensors transmit to the chipset via bluetooth; this data is written
 to the MicroSD card and sent to ground in real-time via APRS
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
Extended Density Lithium Ion Battery 
\series default
22 hour projected life
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
PLEASE NOTE The nature of this chipset is such that any existing scientific
 instrument can be added to the payload with minimal effort, weight allowing.
\end_layout

