\begin_layout Section
Software
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Project CODENAME team has already written and tested a comprehensive
 operational script for the payload.
 By serializing all data sent by APRS, the payload is able to transmit 2
 times the amount of data of typical APRS systems, with less power consumption.
 The program is also written and run natively on the chipset, reducing power
 consumption even further.
 A program to quickly deserialize the data has also been constructed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Part*
Ground Station
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Project CODENAME has two independent methods for predicting weather patterns
 and ballon flight path, both of which have been proven effective in the
 field.
 The team also has direct ties to the Office of Congresswoman Kristi Noem,
 which is expected to simplify negotiations with the FAA tremendously.
\end_layout

